replyContent: The pro version and the the free version are exactly the same when it comes to streaming. There's no source code difference. MP4 and mkv are media containers so your client device must be able to play the codec that the file requires. Not all the devices reproduce all the codec H.264, H.265 etc. Please check which kind of codecs your client support

content: It gets buggy with large vids
replyContent: Usually this problem is related to the WiFi router, and the quality of your video. If you try to send really high resolution videos through a 802.11 n wifi network if the signal is not good you will experience some jumps in the image. The best solution usually is to wire the client to your router through ethernet wire.
